It's clear from all the letters I received when this dialogue went down that a lot of people value this site and don't want to see it disappear.<br><br>
What I've seen on this site at its best is a tremendously diverse group of people willing to honor and learn from their differences, rather than turn them into reasons for hate and ridicule.  I don't want that to stop. We're going to give it another try, this time with some help.<br><br>
Arthur Varanelli, a long-time participant in the dialogues here, and Bob Isbell, a more recent but very active participant, have very generously offered to facilitate the discussions that take place here.  Not babysitters -- every one here is an adult.  Not enforcers of the &quot;rules&quot; -- if this dialogue is going to be meaningful, it really needs to be self-regulating.<br><br>
I have just asked them to keep an eye on things and, by personal example and persuasion, try to keep it constructive.<br><br>
We thought it might help if we opened up two new threads: one to talk about some basic groundrules that everyone can agree on, and one to talk about &quot;fire fights&quot; like the one that broke out about 10 days ago -- how they happen and how they can be avoided in the future.<br><br>
Thanks to all for hanging in there.
